(1 comment)
Seems okay for the nvmesensor bits, though it does seem to affect only `.cpp` files and not clean anything out of `.hpp`s. Any thoughts there?

HeaderFilterRegex might be broken in the clang config in this repo (and it doesn't match what I have in bmcweb).  I think that's just because we're missing the addtion of as_system() to keep it from trying to format dependency headers.  I'll take a look, but I think this patch is still a baseline improvement, and at least keeps cpp files correct.

> I think this patch is still a baseline improvement, and at least keeps cpp files correct.

Yep. Only gave a +1 so others could inspect what's going on, given it hits approximately everything.
Doesn't look like it was HeaderFilterRegex.... I opened that up and it still didn't make changes.  It's going to have to be a problem for another day.
Acknowledged
lgtm - just a little surprised where gpiod landed. Give my +1
It is not a problem, just little surprised that this ended up here.
